<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3472] add back Document.getValues()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3472</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m porting some code to trunk&apos;s new Doc/Field apis, and i keep running into this pattern:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;String[] values = doc.getValues(&quot;field&quot;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But with the new apis, this becomes a little too verbose:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;IndexableField[] fields = doc.getFields(&quot;field&quot;);
String[] values = new String[fields.length];
for (int i = 0; i &amp;lt; values.length; i++) {
  values[i] = fields[i].stringValue();
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think we should probably add back the sugar api (with the same name) ?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
